cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with the problem of drawing graphs on few lines and planes, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves complexity theory and hardness results, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as well. The use of parameterized complexity and fixed-parameter tractability also suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper involves graph theory and combinatorics, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GT (Graph Theory) as well.
